Express Router Functions – Complete Reference
What is Express Router?

An Express Router is a mini Express application used to:

Create modular routes

Organize large applications

Reuse routing logic

const express = require('express');
const router = express.Router();

1. router.METHOD() Function
Purpose

Handles HTTP requests of a specific method.

Syntax
router.get(path, callback);
router.post(path, callback);
router.put(path, callback);
router.delete(path, callback);

Example
router.get('/users', (req, res) => {
  res.send('User List');
});

Mounted in App
app.use('/api', router);

Final URL
/api/users

2. router.all() Function
Purpose

Handles all HTTP methods for a given route.

Example
router.all('/test', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Works for all methods');
});

Use Case

Authentication checks

Logging

Route-level middleware

3. router.param() Function
Purpose

Runs middleware whenever a route parameter is present.

Syntax
router.param(paramName, callback);

Example
router.param('id', (req, res, next, id) => {
  console.log('User ID:', id);
  next();
});

router.get('/user/:id', (req, res) => {
  res.send(`User ${req.params.id}`);
});

4. router.route() Function
Purpose

Creates chainable route handlers for the same path.

Example
router.route('/student')
  .get((req, res) => res.send('Get Student'))
  .post((req, res) => res.send('Add Student'))
  .put((req, res) => res.send('Update Student'));

Advantage

Clean and readable code

Groups logic of same route

5. router.use() Function
Purpose

Adds middleware to the router.

Syntax
router.use([path], middleware);

Example
router.use((req, res, next) => {
  console.log('Router middleware');
  next();
});

Mounting
app.use('/api', router);

Folder Structure (Real MERN Project)
backend/
 ├── routes/
 │    └── userRoutes.js
 ├── controllers/
 ├── models/
 └── app.js

Complete Router Example
const express = require('express');
const router = express.Router();

// Middleware
router.use((req, res, next) => {
  console.log('Request received');
  next();
});

// Param middleware
router.param('id', (req, res, next, id) => {
  console.log('ID:', id);
  next();
});

// Routes
router.get('/users', (req, res) => {
  res.send('All Users');
});

router.route('/user/:id')
  .get((req, res) => res.send('Get User'))
  .put((req, res) => res.send('Update User'))
  .delete((req, res) => res.send('Delete User'));

module.exports = router;
